{"id": 1423, "title": "Ticket #1423: Hibernation broken on UNIX", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen the startd invokes the power_state executable to switch power states, it does this with PRIV_CONDOR_FINAL.  This works in Windows, but in UNIX, root privs are required.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\nActually, it's even worse than above...  Seems that some hack code I put in to test my other work didn't get replaced with real code that Ben was working on...  I'm doing a minimal rework to get it all functional, replacing my_system() with Create_Process(), etc.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2010-Jun-04 09:24:37 by nleroy:</em> <br/>\n\nFor the 7.4.3, I've implemented a simple fix that just wraps the my_system() call with root privs.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1426\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1426'); return false;\" title=\"Finish rework of hibernation\">#1426</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nFinish rework of hibernation</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Aug-05 17:11</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/22677f7d765fa0162a59c6d6bd902c226b56c8ab\">[25630]</a></span>: Documented fix to <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1423\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1423'); return false;\" title=\"Hibernation broken o